{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"cf8a1519-9309-4aba-a2c3-80333b39542b","content":"Here's the correct attribute for each framework:\n\n**MSTest**\n```csharp\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**xUnit**\n```csharp\n[Fact(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\n// or for theory:\n[Theory(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**NUnit**\n```csharp\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**TUnit**\n```csharp\n[Skip(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\nAll four will mark the test as skipped/ignored in test results rather than silently not running it, so you'll see them flagged in your test output.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"25b41867-b25a-4a37-90d2-faf2c0d4c3f4","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about test-skipping attributes across four .NET test frameworks. This is a knowledge question I can answer directly without needing tools.","outputTokens":207,"requestId":"CFCF:12531F:14A434E:17E71E2:69EC1324"},"id":"45145f2b-3489-4df2-ae83-4f3b02d82a47","timestamp":"2026-04-25T01:04:41.329Z","parentId":"8227ba6a-f551-4495-96f6-1f1cecfb51da"}
